***#Lewis Leaps
##by Kendal Bond

Lewis could feel the humming in his *skin*, the generator pulsed so. The indicators remaied amber - standy during preparations - but seemed to glow brighter and brighter as time went by. Almost unexpectedly, the board went green.
"Time to go." Lewis mumbled to themselves, as he reached for the engage switch.
With one deft motion, Lewis turned on the drive - ***and leapt!
The myriad of known and unknown possibilities surged through them, as spactime itself became a mere shadow, vision blinking to a seemingly eternal black.

...

Stars! Unrecognizable constallations! The Leap had been taken.
